description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialist Physiotherapist - 32.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting new opportunity for a Physiotherapist with an interest and experience in neurology to join our Responsive Neuro Services, based at Horsham Hospital. You will be part of a large, friendly, dynamic multidisciplinary team, delivering rehabilitation to patients in their own homes and in a community outpatient setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A high level of clinical support from peers and senior staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encouragement to continue professional and personal development with an active in-service training programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent established relationships with other community services in Horsham, Crawley and Mid Sussex&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 18 months&#39; postgraduate rotational experience in the NHS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience of treating neurological conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An enthusiasm and interest in neuro-rehabilitation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As this is a community post, you must be able to &lt;span&gt;work autonomously as well as part of a team, and &lt;/span&gt;have the ability to travel independently in order to access visits. A full driving licence and access to a car is essential, as well as a willingness to travel across the patch (Horsham, Crawley and Mid Sussex).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Karen Barratt&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clincal Lead Physiotherapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: karenbarratt@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01403 620444&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that Karen works Wed, Thurs and Fri.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If Karen is not available, please ask to speak to one of the team&#39;s Physiotherapists as they will be able to give you further information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
